CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rOyFgz7QOgNxLOZuw_uDC
SUMMARY:MOHAI Mercantile Literary Series - Seattle's Locks and Ship Canal
DTSTAMP:20260317T213915Z
DTSTART:20260325T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Register ➞ https://bit.ly/3NbLLJX  MOHAI Mercantile is proud to
	 host the official book launch event for Seattle’s Locks and Ship Canal wi
	th local historians David B. Williams and Jennifer Ott! This portable guid
	e from UW Press and HistoryLink is an introduction to the engineering marv
	el of the Ballard locks\, and a primer on the history of the ship canal. H
	ear from the authors about the tumultuous history of one of Seattle’s defi
	ning projects\, and the dramatic changes it brought to the city’s economy\
	, neighborhoods\, and natural environment. Doors open at 6 pm for music an
	d mingling. Food and drink available for purchase. Conversation and Q&A be
	gin at 7 pm\, followed by a book signing with the authors.\n\nhttps://seat
	oday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mohai-mercantile-literary-series-seattle
	-s-locks-and-ship-canal/18252331/2026-03-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Even
	ts
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/mohai-mercantile-literary
	-series-seattle-s-locks-and-ship-canal/18252331/2026-03-24T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
